ABUJA – Moves to woo stakeholders in the University system may be paying off as the Chief of Staff to the President, Prof. Ibrahim Gambari is currently meeting with all the unions within the university system. The meeting which was convened by the President, Muhammadu Buhari is connected to finding amicable resolutions to the crisis rocking the nation’s tertiary institutions, especially the industrial action embarked upon by the Academic Staff Union of Universities ASUU, the Senior Staff Association of Nigerian Universities SSANU, the Non Academic Staff Union of University and Allied Institutions NASU, the National Association of Academic Technologists NAAT among others. Among those participating at the meeting includes the Minister for Labour and Employment, Dr Chris Ngige, executive members of the university unions, the President of the Nigeria Labour Congress, Ayuba Wabba, the Minister of Education, Adamu Adamu, and officials of the National Salaries Incomes and Wages Commission. -Advertisement- Recall that ASUU and sister unions within the Universities downed tools several weeks ago over discrepancies in the implementation of the Intergrated Personnel Payroll and Information System IPPIS as well as grievances around revitalization funds for institutions. Details later.